HEADWORD: Feu
<hw>Feu</hw> <pr>(f⟦umac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 2d
<er>Feud</er>, and <er>Fee</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>A
free and gratuitous right to lands made to one for service to be
performed by him; a tenure where the vassal, in place of military
services, makes a return in grain or in money.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

